When Monsieur Dior was in his 20s, the creative intuition inside him was blossoming as he frequented cabarets and festive events where artists inspired him to quit his political science studies. Tap on the card to learn more about Monsieur Dior's life!

Did you know the history behind Monsieur Dior's lucky star? Discovered on the street of Faubourg Saint Honoré in Paris, this recurring symbol of the House was a sign for Monsieur Dior. Tap on the card to learn all about it!

Indicative of the #DiorMenFall 2023 https://t.co/41F1mpz6nM focus on a past-informed future, Kim Jones translated Monsieur Dior's famous 'Junon' couture gown of 1949 into an embroidered tank top. Up next: take a closer look. https://t.co/85R9rmhBs3

Text:
JISOO was in Paris earlier this week to attend the unveiling of the #DiorSS23 collection https://t.co/SNznVrrfG5 by Maria Grazia Chiuri. As we get ready to bring you her show day video diary, see some shots of our global ambassador for fashion and beauty!
© Pierre Mouton https://t.co/0n325ogrMA

Choreographers Imre and Marne Van Opstal relate the story of the dance performance created for the #DiorSS23 by Maria Grazia Chiuri https://t.co/SNznVrJoUd show, a passionate piece to complement the collection. Find the full video soon on our YouTube channel. https://t.co/pjeSFjVpEc

Screen-printed with a crosshatched torso motif, these silicone tops were part of the costumes specially produced for the #DiorSS23 by Maria Grazia Chiuri https://t.co/SNznVrrfG5 show dance performance. Stay tuned for the video about its creation. https://t.co/ZeOZKLQ6he

A highpoint of this week's #DiorSS23 by Maria Grazia Chiuri https://t.co/SNznVrJoUd show, the captivating dance performance choreographed by Imre and Marne Van Opstal played out amid the Eva Jospin-created set. Up next, a focus on the costumes. https://t.co/rMDmgvnCwP

Learn about Catherine de' Medici's outsize influence on French fashion, politics and culture - and, of course, on #DiorSS23 by Maria Grazia Chiuri - by catching the complete film, featuring historian Céline Borello, soon on our YouTube channel https://t.co/CODd4JRHXZ. https://t.co/6hBsDu30Sb

Having performed live at the #DiorSS23 by Maria Grazia Chiuri show, don't miss the takeover by charismatic dancer duo Toon Lobach and Chloé Albaret to be found in our Instagram Story highlights.
© Sophie Carre

The things one can do with cardboard! Be astounded by the making of the magnificent Baroque grotto that the artist Eva Jospin created as the centerpiece of the #DiorSS23 by Maria Grazia Chiuri show. Find the full film soon on our YouTube channel https://t.co/CODd4JRHXZ. https://t.co/pfRjtN0Sja

The work of artist Eva Jospin, the Baroque grotto for the #DiorSS23 by Maria Grazia Chiuri show https://t.co/CODd4JAEVZ represents a whole different kind of #DiorSavoirFaire. Stay tuned for the video detailing its inspiration and creation. https://t.co/oPq3wUsnVH

An audience-free tour through Tuesday's #DiorSS23 by Maria Grazia Chiuri showspace https://t.co/CODd4JRHXZ means all the more opportunity to be blown away by the stupefying Baroque scenography by Eva Jospin. More on that to come!
If you’ve missed seeing the live unveiling of the sumptuous #DiorSS23 by Maria Grazia Chiuri collection, check out the show now on our YouTube channel https://t.co/CODd4JA76r. https://t.co/VD4eoxsvjg
Which one of these #DiorSS23 by Maria Grazia Chiuri https://t.co/CODd4JRHXZ accessories is on your list?

When Maria Grazia Chiuri lightened things up for #DiorSS23 https://t.co/CODd4JRHXZ, an irresistible new top handle bag style and chunky cameo ring were some of the irresistible results. https://t.co/uBXMJsrm5v

A new collection, a new abundance of must-haves! For #DiorSS23 https://t.co/CODd4JA76r, Maria Grazia Chiuri transformed the 'lady D-Joy' with tooled leather and put platforms on strappy shoes. https://t.co/2mJLB1UeZe

As a counterpoint to the amount of dark tones on the #DiorSS23 by Maria Grazia Chiuri https://t.co/SNznVrIR4F show, lighter looks in crisp cottons offer a subtle take on the Catherine de' Medici references through full-sleeved shirting and a sporty corset with slouchy pants.
#PFW https://t.co/cHMFZJtc09

With all the deftness that #DiorSavoirFaire represents, inside the ateliers the petites mains were busy realizing a variety of dresses in lace that would make their debut on the #DiorSS23 by Maria Grazia Chiuri https://t.co/SNznVrIR4F runway.
© Sophie Carre https://t.co/lUuUf9sjQL

Crinolines, corsets, lace and embroideries combine with #DiorSavoirFaire aplomb for #DiorSS23 by Maria Grazia Chiuri https://t.co/SNznVrJoUd referencing Catherine de' Medici with more than a New Look nod. Stay tuned for a lesson in history and handwork.
© Sophie Carre https://t.co/5ndzlJbnqX

An inspired synchronicity with the House's signature silhouette was one of the results when the figure of Catherine de' Medici made her way onto the mood board for #DiorSS23 by Maria Grazia Chiuri https://t.co/SNznVrIR4F collection. Up next: a look at the #DiorSavoirFaire.

Text:
Natalie Portman nailed her front-row look for Tuesday's #DiorSS23 by Maria Grazia Chiuri show https://t.co/SNznVrIR4F. The longtime Dior Beauty face found a flawless balance between mysterious allure and enviable elegance.
#PFW https://t.co/ykjvYwlN3J
(Re)experience the finale of Tuesday's #DiorSS23 by Maria Grazia Chiuri show https://t.co/SNznVrIR4F, a dark and distilled detour through the history of Paris and the House.

The embrace of lace for #DiorSS23 https://t.co/SNznVrrfG5 by Maria Grazia Chiuri reflects a recurring theme throughout the House's history, this byword for femininity explored by the founding couturier and his successors using the inventiveness of incredible #DiorSavoirFaire. https://t.co/ureKbFvxqI

Some close-ups in the atelier taken ahead of the #DiorSS23 https://t.co/SNznVrIR4F by Maria Grazia Chiuri show spotlight how the construction of a dress bodice in a medley of lace demands a #DiorSavoirFaire all its own. https://t.co/IvYgcrJfeW

One of the multiple references linking the House's heritage with the figure of Catherine de' Medici, in the #DiorSS23 collection https://t.co/SNznVrrfG5 the multitude of motifs and colors of lace became a creative canvas for Maria Grazia Chiuri.
#PFW https://t.co/whhOxfBlIS

Indispensable and elemental, the flowers punctuating #DiorSS23 https://t.co/SNznVrJoUd by Maria Grazia Chiuri trace an unbroken lineage back to the founding couturier whose sensibility was shaped by his love of gardens and who regularly named creations after his beloved blooms. https://t.co/tKOKQ4r2Jb

In the atelier, a lighthanded lesson in #DiorSavoirFaire illuminates some of the work required to make this lace-trimmed #DiorSS23 floral dress by Maria Grazia Chiuri https://t.co/SNznVrIR4F. https://t.co/T7QNAEyCkL

Following the dark opening of the #DiorSS23 https://t.co/TspPGA1HKL by Maria Grazia Chiuri show, flowers introduced a more gentle note, from sun-faded violet prints to the lush jacquard of a Tassarini et Chatel by Lelièvre 19th-century archival design.
#PFW https://t.co/aL8GA84xsG

Uncover the full story of the Paris map motif that peppers the newly unveiled #DiorSS23 collection https://t.co/SNznVrJoUd, courtesy of Maria Grazia Chiuri herself, and Soizic Pfaff, head of Dior Heritage.
© Mélinda Triana 
Special thanks to La Bibliothèque nationale de France https://t.co/XHnK7dyNfp

Head to our Instagram account https://t.co/TspPGA1HKL now to check out the illuminating takeover by dancers Chloé Albaret and Toon Lobach who performed in the ​​Imre and Marne van Opstal-choreographed piece at Tuesday's #DiorSS23 by Maria Grazia Chiuri show. https://t.co/UF4VTzNGHj

A famous 1730s representation of the French capital has a long history at the House, from a scarf print to a backdrop for the 'Mexique' couture gown. Up next: a video revealing its origins and role for #DiorSS23 by Maria Grazia Chiuri https://t.co/SNznVrIR4F.

Tranquil tones are in the majority for #DiorCouture Autumn-Winter 2022-2023 by Maria Grazia Chiuri, with tone-on-tone tree of life embroideries and lace insets providing a serene sort of deceptively understated ornamentation.

The innovative overlap of savoir-faire techniques for #DiorCouture Autumn-Winter 2022-2023 by Maria Grazia Chiuri https://t.co/wbre4Ibwya means that embellishments like embroidery and passementerie become almost indistinguishable. https://t.co/NmbAEm4OVo

Turn your attention to two of the #DiorCouture Autumn-Winter 2022-2023 dresses by Maria Grazia Chiuri https://t.co/5ezVhYa9Gv featuring stunning smocking, the technique of gathering fabric into narrow origami-like decorative folds with tiny stitches. https://t.co/mInWW7rhi0

The Mizza leopard motif gets its name from Mizza Bricard, a supremely elegant but somewhat mysterious woman, who Monsieur Dior regarded as his muse, and who always had some leopard somewhere on her outfit, frequently as a print on the scarf permanently wrapping her wrist. https://t.co/i1XGOrCZ86

At 'Monsieur Dior', the virtuosity of both culinary and couture savoir-faire inspired the couturier's designs bearing sugary names https://t.co/qYqWRn6dtO. Reinterpreted by Jean Imbert, the most emblematic French cakes feature Dior symbols in edible form.
#Dior30Montaigne

The Dior 30 Montaigne restaurant https://t.co/qYqWRnnOlm, Monsieur Dior, embodies the French art of living combining simplicity with elegance. French chef Jean Imbert and collaborator Antony Clémot draw from the heritage of the House for the menu. 
#Dior30Montaigne

Among the treasures at La Galerie Dior in the reopened #Dior30Montaigne, is the cabine. House models spent time between fittings and dressed for the frenzied shows which took place over several days. Stay tuned for the video of this emblematic space. https://t.co/0L53vPrAzx

Important symbols to Monsieur Dior and the House come together at La Galerie Dior in the newly reopened #Dior30Montaigne to pay tribute to the legacy of Dior through this exhibition space. Book your visit to the Galerie Dior https://t.co/NdsYdYxE0B. https://t.co/VbPowGEGqm

In a breathtaking black dress, our Global Ambassador JISOO attended the Dior Fall 2022 show by Maria Grazia Chiuri. The sheer lace detailing and full tulle skirt made for a fantastical look. Watch her get ready for the show https://t.co/DBcXX9cc5x. 
#DiorFall22

#DiorFall22

#DiorMenFall https://t.co/qGLFNLEQQS

Discover the Dior men's Fall 2022 collection by Kim Jones, blending Parisian refinement with the modern casualness of American sportswear, available now on our website and in your nearest Dior boutique.

#DiorFall22

From skateboarding to cycling, a sportswear spirit epitomized by these Dior Vibe pieces pulses through Fall 2022 by Maria Grazia Chiuri https://t.co/EKOmASM00g, reflecting the active lifestyles lived by the liberated Dior women of today.

Exemplified by the campaign, Fall 2022 by Maria Grazia Chiuri is a celebration of community, solidarity and sisterhood, a theme highlighted by its unveiling at Seoul's pioneering Ewha Womans University. Tap the visuals to shop the collection!
#DiorFall22
Discover on our website and in your nearest Dior boutique the powerful femininity of the Dior Fall 2022 collection by Maria Grazia Chiuri as captured here through the lens of Alice Mann.

"Transmitting savoir-faire, education and sisterhood is fundamental to Dior, and we must enable the younger generations of women to become talents of tomorrow. Ewha Womans University is the ideal partner."
Pietro Beccari, Chairman and CEO of Christian Dior Couture
#DiorFall22 https://t.co/YAr2PFAENl

The pioneering 136-year-old Ewha Womans University in Seoul welcomes Women@Dior as an opportunity to provide students with the means to enhance their inner growth, supportively mentoring them to become future leaders and build a sustainable society for all.
#DiorFall22 https://t.co/t7HVgXUq07

Following the Fall 2022 show there, the House partners with Seoul's Ewha Womans University for the Women@Dior mentoring and educational program, the focus of a conference featuring Maria Grazia Chiuri. Tap the card to watch the full video on our YouTube channel!
#DiorFall22

Korean designer Jeonghwa Seo reinterprets his characteristically minimal forms with the furniture he created specially for the newly-opened Dior concept store in Seoul's Seongsu-dong district, using traditional sedge weaving and basalt masonry techniques.

Tour new Dior concept store in Seoul's Seongsu-dong district, sensorially stunning in metal and glass, featuring the new Fall 2022 collection by Maria Grazia Chiuri, a dedicated Dior Book Tote room, Dior Café immersive digital experience, and much more.

With Fall 2022 unveiled in Seoul, Maria Grazia Chiuri spotlighted the underappreciated role of women in the House's history. Uncover their story, from the bravery of Catherine Dior to the business acumen of Raymonde Zehnacker, in the full video on our YouTube channel.
#DiorFall22

With hand-painting, pleating, draping and more, see some of the savoir-faire of the costumes by Maria Grazia Chiuri for the ballet dancers in the Angelin Preljocaj-directed film 'Nuit Romaine', soon available on our YouTube channel https://t.co/gPYRZdXN1U.
#InternationalDanceDay https://t.co/UJ6J7HJA6X

The House’s history of design for ballet began with Monsieur Dior himself who, in November 1947, on the urging of friends Christian Bérard and Henri Sauguet, costumed 'Treize Danses', choreographed by Roland Petit for the Théâtre des Champs-Elysées on Avenue Montaigne. https://t.co/Fn6HGvBFvW

Hear Maria Grazia Chiuri discuss the creative challenges and joys of designing for ballet, as we get ready to unveil 'Nuit Romaine', the Angelin Preljocaj-directed film on our YouTube channel https://t.co/gPYRZdXN1U today, April 29, at 3pm CET.

#InternationalDanceDay

Did you know that Dior has a long history with dance? ​​From Leslie Caron to Margot Fonteyn, many celebrated practitioners of the art form have been dressed by the House. This shared spirit encompasses a quest for modernity, movement and an active participation in life. https://t.co/j1GEils64J

Get ready for ‘Nuit Romaine’, costumed by Maria Grazia Chiuri, on our YouTube channel https://t.co/gPYRZdXN1U for #InternationalDanceDay on April 29, at 3pm CET, as Eleonora Abbagnato from @OperaRoma explains what makes Italian dancers different.

Text:
Less than 10% of all plastic is recycled, so the majority persists in the environment.
Plastic is everywhere – from the deepest ocean trenches to the highest mountain peaks. It is in the air we breathe, the food we eat and the water we drink.
#EarthDay #DiorParley https://t.co/t2Ynb2qYaH

Did you know that more than 10 million metric tons of plastic waste enters the oceans every year, roughly a truckload a minute?
Billions of plastic items are created from oil and gas to be used for moments and then thrown "away" – but they never biodegrade.
#EarthDay #DiorParley https://t.co/qWCqVLdOWQ

Text: Constantly reaching new heights, Margo is an inspiration to us all. Which athlete that we collaborated with for #DiorVibe would you like us to focus on next?

Did you know that in 2016 Margo won both the Bouldering and Lead Climbing events at the World Youth Championships in China? In 2017 she went on to be the first woman in history to climb a 9a+ (5.15a) route. A feat that exemplifies the determination of the Dior Vibe.

Text:
Stand-collar jackets worn with shorts or pants offer new takes on tailoring, with a variation on the 'Tailleur Oblique' enhanced by embroidery. The #DiorEyewear sunglasses feature hinges formed from the reborn 1960s CD Diamond monogram.
© Rafael Pavarotti

The American Southwest mood that courses through #DiorSummer22  https://t.co/5XNdX54gxa by Kim Jones is hinted at in a bandana print shirt and the earthy shades of #DiorB30 sneakers and a Dior Saddle, while metallics crop up as trim and a 'CD Icon' bracelet.
© Rafael Pavarotti https://t.co/g99t4or0IB

From a gray 'Dior Lingot' duffel bag and 'Hit The Road' backpack to a dusky pink sweater, the revived CD Diamond motif from the 1960s provides graphic punctuation to #DiorSummer22 pieces https://t.co/5XNdX54gxa by Kim Jones.
© Rafael Pavarotti https://t.co/2ofTzfcPED

Explore Dior Men's Summer 2022 by Kim Jones https://t.co/5XNdX4MF8A and revel in the psychedelic mood of its new campaign video. Emulating hip-hop imagery, 70s energy, and the desert light into sharp tailoring, knitwear, and 'CD' diamond motifs with a new attitude.
© Axel Morin

See some of the arresting applications of the revived 1960s geometric CD Diamond monogram for #DiorSummer22 https://t.co/5XNdX54gxa by Kim Jones, from a briefcase to 'Dior Lingot' duffel and 'Hit The Road' backpack, as well as on 'B23' high-tops.
© Rafael Pavarotti

Discover the new campaign for #DiorSummer22 by Kim Jones https://t.co/5XNdX54gxa, evoking the colors, codes and arid landscapes of the American Southwest with fringing details, a CD Diamond motif belt bag and Dior Oblique-accented #DiorB27 sneakers.
© Rafael Pavarotti https://t.co/3RVsEYzEpK

See the #DiorMaison cushions https://t.co/rjBPj4Vrxq embroidered with 'Athens' designs by Pietro Ruffo for #DiorCruise 2022 by Maria Grazia Chiuri, featuring florals and the founding couturier's lucky star, while others are adorned with 'Dior Étoile' and toile de Jouy motifs. https://t.co/5Mz0hxjz69

Referencing the iconic Paris address, New Look debut and Dior savoir-faire, varsity-inspired, 'Christian Dior Atelier' pieces https://t.co/oZuLiEV4pS from #BabyDior by Cordelia de Castellane echo #DiorSpring22 men's designs by Kim Jones.
